  "notes": "Santali (Jharkhand, West Bengal, Odisha, Bihar). Austroasiatic, Munda branch — unrelated to IA or Dravidian. Written officially in Ol Chiki script (invented 1925 by Raghunath Murmu); also Latin and Devanagari. Phonemic aspiration in stops; glottalized vowels in checked syllables. No retroflex consonants (unlike IA neighbours).",
